1286
01:59:17,026 --> 01:59:18,736
<i>It has always been enough...</i>

1287
01:59:19,820 --> 01:59:22,448
<i>to be part of the natural sequence
of things.</i>

1288
01:59:23,866 --> 01:59:25,159
<i>Sure as the tides.</i>

1289
01:59:25,993 --> 01:59:27,369
<i>Nature my guide.</i>

1290
01:59:31,999 --> 01:59:34,043
<i>The marsh knows all about death...</i>

1291
01:59:37,046 --> 01:59:39,673
<i>and doesn't necessarily
define it as tragedy.</i>

1292
01:59:40,841 --> 01:59:42,259
<i>Certainly not a sin.</i>

1293
01:59:44,011 --> 01:59:48,057
<i>It understands that every creature
does what it must to survive.</i>

1294
01:59:50,726 --> 01:59:53,896
<i>And that sometimes, for prey to live...</i>

1295
01:59:55,105 --> 01:59:56,857
<i>its predator must die.</i>

1296
02:00:25,135 --> 02:00:26,470
<i>I am the marsh now.</i>

1297
02:00:28,555 --> 02:00:30,140
<i>I am the feather of an egret.</i>

1298
02:00:31,433 --> 02:00:33,936
<i>I am every shell washed upon the shore.</i>

1299
02:00:37,731 --> 02:00:39,108
